Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.93,0:01:47.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}"Genbee Ski Lodge"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.18,0:01:53.22,MovieDerpsub,,0000,0000,0000,,Though my body may die,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.22,0:01:58.55,MovieDerpsub,,0000,0000,0000,,know that my spirit will someday be revived with the snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.99,0:02:06.12,MovieDerpsub,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Love of the Snow Woman
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.99,0:02:06.12,MovieDerpsub,,0000,0000,0000,,To Be Continued
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.97,0:02:10.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's always such a powerful show!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.34,0:02:15.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.81,0:02:18.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a mechanical doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.01,0:02:20.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have some tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.11,0:02:21.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A doll, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.78,0:02:24.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really well-made!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.89,0:02:31.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a rare thing you have!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.26,0:02:35.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The previous owners of this place left it behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.27,0:02:36.99,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Genbee Kitamura (65)\NLodge Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.27,0:02:36.99,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo Kitamura (61)\NGenbee's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.66,0:02:38.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you watching the Snow Woman on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.36,0:02:40.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.10,0:02:42.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was really scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.00,0:02:44.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Snow Women aren't for real!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.90,0:02:46.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.84,0:02:51.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This area is famous for its Snow Woman sightings!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.51,0:02:55.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows, maybe she'll even show up tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.12,0:02:59.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.80,0:03:04.01,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko Kinoshita (26)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.72,0:03:04.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really staying {\i1}here{\i0}, Yoko?\NHow is this a "great inn"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.97,0:03:08.48,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko Asanuma (26)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.01,0:03:08.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no other place to stay,\Nand the bus already left!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.46,0:03:12.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.20,0:03:16.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello! I made a reservation the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.07,0:03:20.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes! Akiko Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0} and Yoko Asanuma-{\i1}san{\i0}, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.60,0:03:25.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming all this way!\NYour skis have already arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.71,0:03:31.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Did you just say "Akiko Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0}"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.08,0:03:33.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! It's really you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.12,0:03:37.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just watching\N"Love of the Snow Woman" on TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:42.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! It's Akiko Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0}, the actress! In the flesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.09,0:03:46.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kogoro Mouri, the detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.33,0:03:52.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! That scene where you throw yourself into the lake was amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.70,0:03:56.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You fell straight for the lake, like, "Whoosh!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.24,0:03:59.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was actually Yoko who did that dive, not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.31,0:04:01.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a stuntwoman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:06.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you act out dangerous scenes\Nin the place of main actors?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:13.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko is my exclusive stuntwoman.\NMy double, you could even say!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:18.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, where might the restroom be?\NIt's so chilly outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.13,0:04:19.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the restroom is—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.96,0:04:22.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At the far end of the hall, on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.97,0:04:29.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does our room have a view of a persimmon tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.61,0:04:32.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, just as you requested!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:38.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hit the hay, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.32,0:04:39.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:44.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}. Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0} said this is her first time here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.15,0:04:47.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So how did she know where the bathroom was?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.93,0:04:52.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're so curious about everything, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.10,0:04:57.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't bathrooms usually always in the same general area?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:00.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially in older buildings like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.94,0:05:08.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope the weather is clear tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.52,0:05:22.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The Snow Woman!\NConan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! The Snow Woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.06,0:05:23.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? The Snow Woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.63,0:05:28.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.89,0:05:33.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be! I saw her!\NI {\i1}know{\i0} I saw her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.30,0:05:35.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the commotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.97,0:05:38.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! I saw the Snow Woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.98,0:05:40.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Snow Woman?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.75,0:05:46.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No one's out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.28,0:05:49.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were just so afraid of the Snow Woman
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.29,0:05:52.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that a pile of snow looked like her to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.22,0:05:56.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? It was just my imagination?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.53,0:06:05.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I'll be back tomorrow evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.30,0:06:07.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'd like to schedule a body massage and a facial!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.91,0:06:10.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.64,0:06:14.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}. Don't forget these.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.31,0:06:15.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.72,0:06:27.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You almost look like a bank robber gang!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.66,0:06:30.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actresses can't afford to be sunburned.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.76,0:06:34.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Move! Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.30,0:06:37.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming through!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.18,0:06:47.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! There's Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0} and Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.22,0:07:02.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mountain weather sure changes fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.86,0:07:05.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This snow came out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.77,0:07:10.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0}! Are you by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:14.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} wanted to ski for a little bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:17.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} sure is full of power!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.17,0:07:21.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she pretends to be full of energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.85,0:07:25.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...but she's actually not well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.25,0:07:26.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.92,0:07:33.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} not being well... Is she sick somehow?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.66,0:07:36.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:43.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.07,0:07:44.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Has Yoko returned yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.70,0:07:46.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.21,0:07:52.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you suppose she caught a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.25,0:08:00.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a real life-saver!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.08,0:08:01.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.42,0:08:03.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a delicious meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:06.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} was coughing. Is she all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.32,0:08:09.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She doesn't seem to have an appetite, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.56,0:08:11.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's resting now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.63,0:08:13.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss! Can we use the bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:18.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, go right ahead! You have it to yourselves until 8:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:19.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.84,0:08:23.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can take a bath after 8:00, Ran-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.31,0:08:25.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you have the men's bath all to yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.32,0:08:38.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}. Are you all right?\NYou really should see a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.96,0:08:42.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'll do that. I think I'll get out for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.26,0:08:45.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I think I'll stay in a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.30,0:08:47.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}! Are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.46,0:08:48.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.50,0:08:52.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say to having an after-bath drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.27,0:08:54.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'd love to!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.14,0:09:00.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so they're making it into a play?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.91,0:09:04.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It received such critical acclaim!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.82,0:09:07.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like on TV, Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s going to play the main character!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.89,0:09:10.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume you're going to be in it too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.59,0:09:14.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but of course! Please come and watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.86,0:09:16.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.19,0:09:17.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'll go to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.93,0:09:22.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I guess there wasn't very much in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.30,0:09:24.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan. Go bring us some beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.84,0:09:28.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already 10:00. The owners are asleep now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.01,0:09:30.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have some whiskey in my room,\Nif you'd prefer that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.64,0:09:31.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.91,0:09:35.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's drink a little more! I'll go get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.68,0:09:41.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.92,0:09:43.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.79,0:09:46.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have fun tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.63,0:09:52.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What about the whiskey?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.30,0:09:56.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it's apparently at the bottom of Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s suitcase,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.20,0:09:59.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so she said she'll bring it to us in a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.37,0:10:01.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} will?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.31,0:10:04.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Is that her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.17,0:10:06.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'll go check.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.95,0:10:09.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.98,0:10:13.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.28,0:10:16.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, still not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.85,0:10:19.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! I think that {\i1}is{\i0} her now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.43,0:10:24.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.50,0:10:29.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The whiskey's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.27,0:10:34.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had so much fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.10,0:10:35.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.77,0:10:38.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Ran-{\i1}san{\i0}. Go on ahead to the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.74,0:10:42.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to check on Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} real quick first.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.31,0:10:43.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.92,0:10:50.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.92,0:10:52.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.26,0:10:57.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't seem to remember that doll being there when I looked earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.33,0:10:58.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.66,0:11:01.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh oh! Did I drink a little too much?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.07,0:11:06.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0} be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.81,0:11:11.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.61,0:11:13.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Snow Woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.21,0:11:14.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.38,0:11:17.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I really did! She was wearing a white kimono!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.81,0:11:20.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}! It's terrible! It's Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:23.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.49,0:11:26.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this! It's Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s will!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:27.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.06,0:11:30.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}"Will"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.33,0:11:30.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was gone when I returned to our room!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.73,0:11:33.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I checked around the building, but I couldn't find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.66,0:11:36.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when I checked our room closer, I found that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.90,0:11:40.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} has lung cancer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.20,0:11:45.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know! But her strange coughing had her worried, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.91,0:11:49.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She says her father suffered from the same illness...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.45,0:11:52.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he died of lung cancer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.72,0:11:57.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She may have been secretly worried she had cancer too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.59,0:12:01.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I want to die as the Snow Woman..."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.99,0:12:05.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the Snow Woman I saw just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.60,0:12:07.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It might've been Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.96,0:12:11.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0}. Contact the police right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.07,0:12:14.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's very cold out! We need to find Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} as quickly as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.94,0:12:15.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.08,0:12:21.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! We're going out to search, too! Get ready right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.21,0:12:22.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:26.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, mister! Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} made a beauty salon appointment!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.45,0:12:29.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would someone committing suicide really schedule an appointment?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.39,0:12:31.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She probably decided to kill herself in the spur of the moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.09,0:12:35.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey!\N- Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.93,0:12:39.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Where are you?!\N- Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.23,0:12:42.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Please say something!\N- Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:45.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.91,0:12:50.44,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The next morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.44,0:12:55.81,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Akiko-san was found dead,\Nwearing her Snow Woman costume.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.65,0:13:08.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}! Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.46,0:13:12.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there's no doubt\Nshe {\i1}is{\i0} Akiko Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:14.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.20,0:13:15.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.57,0:13:19.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kogoro Mouri, a detective.\NI was staying in the same lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.59,0:13:23.09,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Kawada\NMikkamachi Police
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.83,0:13:23.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You're that famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.91,0:13:26.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kawada, of the Mikkamachi Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.74,0:13:31.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, there was a sedative bottle lying next to Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.28,0:13:37.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} brought the whiskey after 10:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.69,0:13:40.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning she committed suicide after then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.36,0:13:45.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the Snow Woman I saw\Nwas probably Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.43,0:13:48.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how the scene looked when we found her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.00,0:13:55.17,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What the—?! Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.17,0:13:56.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since this was a suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.81,0:14:00.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,help from the Great Detective Mouri\Nprobably won't be needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.32,0:14:09.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Signs that someone climbed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.66,0:14:21.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.73,0:14:26.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Where is the previous owner of this lodge now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:29.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? The previous owner?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.97,0:14:32.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He lives in the next village over now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.41,0:14:34.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.48,0:14:38.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.82,0:14:40.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.15,0:14:43.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This was no suicide! It was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.32,0:14:45.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And the killer was that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.59,0:14:53.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to send the body off for mandatory autopsy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.33,0:14:56.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it's pretty clear it's a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.33,0:14:57.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.54,0:15:05.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You must {\i1}not{\i0} take that body away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.41,0:15:11.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko Kinoshita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s death was a murder, not a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:15.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}! What evidence\Ndo you have it was a murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.09,0:15:16.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Kawada.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.59,0:15:21.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closer at the photographs from when her body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.53,0:15:28.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s hair is inside the collar of the kimono.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.10,0:15:33.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A person seeking out death wouldn't wear clothes so brazenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.64,0:15:36.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone changed her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.07,0:15:37.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.44,0:15:40.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you, Yoko Asanuma-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.45,0:15:47.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}! You know Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} wasn't in a normal state of mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.25,0:15:51.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt she worried about her hair\Nwhen putting on the kimono!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.89,0:15:54.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Kawada.\NPlease look at the photographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.93,0:15:59.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears her body was buried quite deeply in the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.63,0:16:05.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The snow started yesterday around 5:00 PM and ended around 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.84,0:16:09.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} had killed herself\Nafter 10:00 last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.74,0:16:13.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,her body wouldn't have been buried in that much snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.65,0:16:18.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And one other thing.\NLook closely at Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s face.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.08,0:16:21.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She has a foundation on to prevent sunburn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.82,0:16:25.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would someone at night,\Nand someone about to commit suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.26,0:16:28.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,really put such a foundation on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.16,0:16:30.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, she does have foundation on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.70,0:16:36.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} was most likely given\Nthe sedative without her realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.77,0:16:41.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And no one else but you could have done that, Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.57,0:16:46.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}! You all saw Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.58,0:16:50.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What we saw was you acting as Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.15,0:16:53.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Acting?! What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.92,0:16:56.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who invited Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} skiing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:16:58.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and booked a room here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.79,0:17:01.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you choose this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.59,0:17:05.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it would be easiest\Nto play two people at once here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.80,0:17:07.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two people at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.53,0:17:11.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You and Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} share similar stature.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.37,0:17:16.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After killing her, you needed to make it appear she was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.81,0:17:19.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you chose this lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.61,0:17:22.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't this Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s first time here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.58,0:17:23.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.82,0:17:28.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You worked here part-time one winter\Nduring your student days.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.62,0:17:32.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The previous owner remembered your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.83,0:17:38.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, you gave her the sedative to knock her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.63,0:17:42.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You then put her in her Snow Woman outfit and left her outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.80,0:17:48.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucky for you, it had just started to snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.01,0:17:53.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what you didn't count on\Nwas the snow stopping soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.18,0:18:00.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. The Snow Woman you saw our first day here was Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.08,0:18:03.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She covered herself with a white kimono to keep from standing out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.45,0:18:05.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as she went to hide another kimono.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.89,0:18:07.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There were two Snow Woman outfits:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.96,0:18:11.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,one for Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} and one for Yoko-{\i1}san{\i0}, the stuntwoman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.70,0:18:15.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She buried one of them in the snow in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.43,0:18:19.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the following day, yesterday evening to be precise,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.10,0:18:23.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she put it on the sleeping Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.88,0:18:30.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you returned here\Nas if nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:34.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} came back, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.02,0:18:39.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You disguised yourself as her\Nas soon as you returned to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.12,0:18:42.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To make it seem like the dead Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} was still quite alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.96,0:18:48.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You climbed to the roof via the persimmon tree outside your window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.23,0:18:51.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As a stuntwoman, that would be simple to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:57.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You then put on Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s ski boots, which you had hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.11,0:19:00.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and returned with her skis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.71,0:19:07.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You also played the role of two people for us in the open-air bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.35,0:19:11.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You, if anyone, can imitate Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.72,0:19:16.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The final touch was the Snow Woman\Nthat Ran saw from the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.66,0:19:20.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were pretending to be Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} as she strode off to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.60,0:19:25.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it look like she had committed suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:30.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and that she had still been alive at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.28,0:19:34.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about the whiskey she brought us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.18,0:19:40.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that was another act of yours.\NWe never saw Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.49,0:19:44.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I received the whiskey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.16,0:19:49.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0} was dead,\Njust who brought the whiskey?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.16,0:19:53.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You chose this lodge for one other reason:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.40,0:19:56.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the mechanical doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.07,0:19:58.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You went to get the whiskey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.70,0:20:02.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you had the mechanical doll bring it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.34,0:20:07.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when I went to look,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.75,0:20:10.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the doll was nowhere to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.45,0:20:13.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it wasn't my imagination;
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.28,0:20:17.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the doll was actually behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.06,0:20:21.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.76,0:20:28.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You later returned the doll to its platform
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.77,0:20:31.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when pretending to use the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.27,0:20:36.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you used the doll to fill in for Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.74,0:20:41.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s fingerprints should be missing from the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.95,0:20:49.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's more proof than anything that she no longer existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.62,0:20:57.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I drugged Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}... and killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.40,0:21:01.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I also wrote the will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.83,0:21:05.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The part about her father's death was true,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.60,0:21:08.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but there was nothing wrong with her at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.57,0:21:10.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.07,0:21:14.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was always being outdone by her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.35,0:21:17.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I made it to the final audition of my very first drama role,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.72,0:21:20.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and lost to Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.12,0:21:22.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was always the same ever since!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.22,0:21:25.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I would always lose to her in the final audition!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.06,0:21:28.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She went on to become a star,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.36,0:21:31.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while all I ever heard was,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.46,0:21:37.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"You look like Akiko Kinoshita.\NWe don't want a copycat show."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.14,0:21:43.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I thought I'd always be her double\Nas long as she was around...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.81,0:23:32.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Snow Man! The Snow Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.50,0:23:50.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! It's you, Sachiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.37,0:23:58.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The old guy fell asleep along the way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.24,0:24:03.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But he was awake until 9:00,\Nchatting with Sachiko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.32,0:24:05.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Her alibi is airtight!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.19,0:24:08.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.11,0:24:14.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.03,0:24:19.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Candy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.25,0:24:20.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next time, the old man's in big trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.60,0:24:22.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That's why Mom ran out on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.60,0:24:23.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Yep.
